    en: "New York General Business Law Article 35-E (Sections 756 through 756-c), known as the Construction Prompt Payment Act, requires owners to pay contractors within 30 days of an approved invoice and contractors to pay subcontractors within 7 days of receipt from the owner. Failure to pay on time triggers statutory interest at 1 percent per month plus attorney's fees. The Act applies to construction contracts over $150,000 on private projects; a parallel statute for public works projects appears in State Finance Law and General Municipal Law. Contractors can suspend work after 10 days of payment default with written notice. Mechanics lien and Trust Fund Act remedies (Lien Law Article 3-A) run alongside."
